global_this_singleton.fix:
Replace the Prisma singleton with the canonical Next.js pattern. The file MUST use `var` (not let or const) in the `declare global` block, and MUST include `// eslint-disable-next-line no-var` to prevent ESLint from flagging the required `var` keyword:

```typescript
import { PrismaClient } from '@prisma/client';

const prismaClientSingleton = () => new PrismaClient();

declare global {
  // eslint-disable-next-line no-var
  var prisma: undefined | ReturnType<typeof prismaClientSingleton>;
}

const prisma = globalThis.prisma ?? prismaClientSingleton();

if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') globalThis.prisma = prisma;

export default prisma;
```

CRITICAL: Using `let` instead of `var` in `declare global` does NOT work — TypeScript requires `var` for global scope augmentation. The `// eslint-disable-next-line no-var` comment is mandatory to prevent ESLint from rejecting the `var` keyword.
